| `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/delhi/app/src/server/extraction/embedding-writeback.ts` | 42 | Creating labels from `record.tb` and `record.id` |
| `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/delhi/app/src/server/descriptions/types.ts` | 1-7 | `DescriptionEntry` containing optional `source?: RecordId` |
| `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/delhi/app/src/server/graph/queries.ts` | 1032-1042 | `getEntityDetail()` returns entity data (which includes `description_entries`) |

The frontend receives `description_entries` as part of the `entity.data` object in the `EntityDetailResponse`, where each entry may contain a `source` field that is a serialized `RecordId` with `{ tb, id }` structure.

